'''''Culture of Death''''' has two distinct meanings:
*A term coined by [[John Paul II]] used in contemporary political discourse in many countries, including the [[United States]] and [[Poland]] to describe certain positions, such as abortion, that contrast with their positions, which they call the [[Culture of Life]].

*A term used in [[Imperialism|Colonial Europe]] to describe [[barbarian|"barbaric"]] cultures which allegedly glorified or worshiped death.  This was then used as a justification for the subjugation and colonization of these cultures.

As can be seen, despite the distinct places and times, both have been used as a [[propaganda]] device to vilify and dehumanize their opponents.

